00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,000
Moot's looking at his hands

1071
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,000
and then it comes down on top of him

1072
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:40,000
and he crumples to the deck, unconscious.

1073
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:41,000
Holy shit.

1074
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:42,000
Sully's turn.

1075
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:47,000
Russ, one quick thing before that happens.

1076
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:50,000
I have a trait as a half-orc.

1077
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:52,000
When I am reduced to zero hit points

1078
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:56,000
but not killed, I can drop to one hit point instead.

1079
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,000
Relentless endurance.

1080
00:40:58,000 --> 00:40:59,000
Go half-orc.

1081
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:01,000
Yeah, that's nice.

1082
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:03,000
OK, retake.

1083
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:05,000
Moot goes down hard.

1084
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:08,000
You hear this like breath

1085
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:12,000
as he kind of like gets back up onto his knees.

1086
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Oh, thank fuck Jesus.

1087
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:15,000
Really cool.

1088
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:16,000
He's still alive.

1089
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:17,000
I'm OK.

1090
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:21,000
Sounded like the captain.

1091
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,000
He was waking up.

1092
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:23,000
Somebody wake up.

1093
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:24,000
Just a little bit.

1094
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:30,000
Sully is going to slash at it again.

1095
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,000
No, he's not.

1096
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:34,000
He's going to reroll that because it was a one.

1097
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,000
Jeez.

1098
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:37,000
Real swings today.

1099
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,000
Yeah.

1100
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,000
OK, that's only a 13.

1101
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,000
Doesn't hit.

1102
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,000
OK.

1103
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:45,000
But then, once per long rest,

1104
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:48,000
Sully, can you shimmer gloom,

1105
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:51,000
which is the dragon-hilt head

1106
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:55,000
of the sword of frightful reflection,

1107
00:41:55,000 --> 00:42:01,000
to make an enemy of my choice become frightened

1108
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:03,000
upon failing a con save.

1109
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,000
All right.

1110
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:07,000
We are killing it with using things today, guys.

1111
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:08,000
We really are.

1112
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,000
I don't know if water can be frightened, though,

1113
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:11,000
but I'm just pulling it out.

1114
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:13,000
Let me check the condition immunities.

1115
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:14,000
Frightened is not listed.

1116
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:18,000
Although, I have to admit, full credit goes to D&D Beyond

1117
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,000
because when I downed my hit points,

1118
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:21,000
it was like, hey, do you want to use this thing?

1119
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:22,000
Oh.

1120
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,000
It's like, oh, yes, I do.

1121
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:25,000
Thanks, D&D Beyond.

1122
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,000
7 on the die plus 4 is 11.

1123
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,000
Sully goes to, like, lean forward

1124
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,000
in, like, a intimidating kind of way,

1125
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:33,000
like, huh, expecting to scare it off.

1126
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:36,000
It's like a little shimmer or, like, ripple in the water.

1127
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:41,000
Can I roll again

1128
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:47,000
because I was given advantage from that rousing speech?

1129
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:49,000
It was inspiring.

1130
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:50,000
OK.

1131
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,000
Good remembering.

1132
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:52,000
I'd already forgotten that happened.

1133
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:53,000
It just came to me.

1134
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,000
You're welcome.

1135
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:55,000
19.

1136
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:56,000
That will hit.

1137
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,000
OK, here we go.

1138
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:58,000
I'm all lost.

1139
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:00,000
10 slashing damage.

1140
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,000
All right.

1141
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,000
Oh.

1142
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:04,000
Well, because I didn't think of it

1143
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:07,000
because I was able to reroll my 1 as my thingy

1144
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:09,000
and it hurt me until after.

1145
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,000
Yeah, that's fair.

1146
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:11,000
I did it.

1147
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,000
You did it.

1148
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:13,000
You strike into it.

1149
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:15,000
It is not frightened, and it is Glim's turn.

1150
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:18,000
Am I able to do an attack

1151
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:21,000
and also touch my friend with my action?

1152
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:22,000
I'd say you're all pretty close.

1153
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,000
I do both of those things?

1154
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:25,000
Like, it's not a bitch.

1155
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:26,000
OK.

1156
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,000
So, yeah, sure.

1157
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,000
It's more of a boat.

1158
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:29,000
No, for sure.

1159
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,000
It's all down to me.

1160
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:31,000
Don't hurt.

1161
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,000
Come on now.

1162
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,000
We've already covered this.

1163
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:34,000
Appreciate it.

1164
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:37,000
OK, then I am going to attack again

1165
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,000
with the Vorpal Sword, which is a 25.

1166
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:42,000
Yep.

1167
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:43,000
Ooh, baby.

1168
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:46,000
Bad roll, but 8 damage.

1169
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:51,000
And then I'm going to use my Lay on Hands pull

1170
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:57,000
to heal up Moot a bit, which is, I have 15.

1171
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,000
So we'll say 14?

1172
00:43:58,000 --> 00:44:00,000
Sally was just being a little bit of a baby.

1173
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:01,000
Yeah.

1174
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:02,000
OK.

1175
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:04,000
Yeah, you strike in and then reach down to Moot,

1176
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:06,000
who's still trying to catch his breath.

1177
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:10,000
This radiant light begins to glow on you, Moot,

1178
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:13,000
and you feel the energy come back.

1179
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:14,000
You're able to catch your breath,

1180
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:16,000
and you feel a little bit more strength in order to...

1181
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:18,000
So wait, do I feel like the same amount of energy

1182
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:21,000
I had before the last time?

1183
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:24,000
Oh, yeah, your wild magic is popping off.

1184
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,000
OK.

1185
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:26,000
Absolutely.

1186
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:28,000
Yeah, I'm talking like physical energy,

1187
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:30,000
not like your tingly bits, your dingleberry energy.

1188
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:32,000
Oh, OK, because that's what I thought you meant,

1189
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:33,000
and I was like, OK.

1190
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:35,000
Yeah, no, but definitely your dingleberry energy

1191
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:37,000
is strong with this one.

1192
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:39,000
I don't approve of that name.

1193
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:43,000
Dorban's still row, row, row.

1194
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:44,000
He's still doing OK.

1195
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:48,000
I feel like we're making good headway.

1196
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:49,000
No.

1197
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:51,000
OK, keep rowing.

1198
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:54,000
We're barely out of the fog.

1199
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:55,000
Moot, your turn.

1200
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:59,000
OK, I guess magic missile again.

1201
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:05,000
Six and four is 10 force damage on that one.

1202
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,000
It hits and then rocks back,

1203
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:10,000
and it slows its pace a little bit at this point.

1204
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:12,000
And roll percentile dice, please.

1205
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,000
That is a 19.

1206
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:17,000
You can cast grease centered on yourself.

1207
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:19,000
It doesn't say you do.

1208
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:20,000
No, it does.

1209
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:23,000
You cast grease centered on yourself.

1210
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:25,000
Because all of a sudden he's got chills

1211
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:27,000
and he's multiplying.

1212
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:29,000
Losing control.

1213
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:31,000
So yeah, your magic missiles go off,

1214
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:33,000
and then, Glim, you're right close to him.

1215
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:36,000
Magic grease covers the ground in a 10-foot square

1216
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:38,000
centered on a point within range

1217
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:40,000
and turns it into difficult terrain for the duration.

1218
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:41,000
When the grease appears,

1219
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:42,000
each creature standing in it

1220
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:44,000
must succeed on a dexterity saving throw

1221
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:45,000
or fall prone.

1222
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:47,000
So we're all like whoop, whoop, whoop, whoop,

1223
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:49,000
on the ground.

1224
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:52,000
Benny Hill starts up, and so,

1225
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:55,000
I mean, 10 feet, so Glim for sure.

1226
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:57,000
Maybe Sully's out of this

1227
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,000
because a lot's happened to him already.

1228
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:00,000
Yeah, yeah, Sully's out of it.

1229
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:01,000
So just Glim.

1230
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,000
Dex saving throw, you said?

1231
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:03,000
Yep.

1232
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:04,000
And it's centered on yourself,

1233
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:06,000
so you gotta make it two there.

1234
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:07,000
16.

1235
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:08,000
14 for Moot.

1236
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:11,000
So it would be against your spell save DC there, Moot.

1237
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,000
Spell save DC's 13.

1238
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,000
It gets slick, so it's difficult terrain,

1239
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:17,000
so half speed movement,

1240
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:20,000
but it's slippery.

1241
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:24,000
But on the positive side,

1242
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:26,000
it's also hard to stand up.

1243
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:27,000
And shiny.

1244
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:28,000
That's right.

1245
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:30,000
And that duration is for one minute.

1246
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:33,000
And we definitely don't want any fire now.

1247
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:34,000
No.

1248
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:38,000
The water elemental's gonna take one more swing at you here.

1249
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:39,000
And try and...

1250
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:41,000
Grease and water repel each other,

1251
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:43,000
like you know when you put...

1252
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:44,000
Yeah, maybe.

1253
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,000
I feel like that's actually helpful for us.

1254
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:47,000
Could be.

1255
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:50,000
Everybody as...

1256
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,000
Yeah, let's do it.

1257
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:54,000
Let's see what happens.

1258
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:57,000
The wave wells up and over the ship

1259
00:46:57,000 --> 00:46:59,000
and slams down on top.

1260
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:01,000
Everybody has to make a...

1261
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,000
Everybody who's on top, which is the three of you,

1262
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:05,000
has to make a strength saving throw.

1263
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:08,000
Why is all the saves the stuff I can't do?

1264
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:11,000
I don't know.

1265
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:12,000
Why are we fighting a water creature

1266
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:14,000
when two of us have so many fire powers?

1267
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,000
Eight.

1268
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:16,000
Russ.

1269
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:19,000
It's like the deck is really stacked against us here.

1270
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:20,000
12.

1271
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:21,000
Eight.

1272
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:22,000
But can I do it again,

1273
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:24,000
because I'm inspired and greasy?

1274
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:25,000
Oh.

1275
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:27,000
The greasy part doesn't help,

1276
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:28,000
but yes.

1277
00:47:28,000 --> 00:47:30,000
I mean, I was inspired as well.

1278
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:32,000
Yeah, I don't think you've used your advantage yet,

1279
00:47:32,000 --> 00:47:33,000
so yeah.

1280
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:34,000
20.

1281
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:35,000
Greasy.

1282
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:37,000
I will stick with the original 12, thank you.

1283
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,000
Okay, on a failure,

1284
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:41,000
a target takes 13 bludgeoning damage.

1285
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:43,000
You don't have to say it like that, Russ.

1286
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,000
Oh God.

1287
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:46,000
So you're gonna take 13 bludgeoning damage.

1288
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:47,000
Okay.

1289
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:49,000
If it is large or smaller,

1290
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:51,000
it is also grappled.

1291
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:53,000
Until this grapple ends,

1292
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:54,000
the target is restrained

1293
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:57,000
and unable to breathe unless it can breathe water.

1294
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:59,000
The saving throw is successful.

1295
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:01,000
The target is pushed out of the elemental space.

1296
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:06,000
So, yeah, Sully and Glim,

1297
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:09,000
you just wash away up to the sides of the deck,

1298
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:10,000
but then you look back

1299
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:13,000
and you see Moot up inside this water elemental,

1300
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:16,000
spinning and churning within it.

1301
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:26,000
So, yeah,

1302
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:31,000
I will stick with the original 12, thank you.

